---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 138
  - Title: Srimad Bhagavatam
    Location: XI v
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Detachment From Place and
    Conditions
  - Union-Identity=Mysterium Magnum=Non-Duality
---
Truly wise is he who is unstirred by praise or blame, by love or hatred. He
is not moved by the opposites of life. Verily does he delight in the blissful
Self.
